s not a special feature of human being, if we saw ourselves from the creator’s point of view\n\n- Sunday\n|\nTo understand what makes you future strong, and what being strong means, is to understand how and why you make choices.\n\n- Bill Jensen, Future Strong\n|\nForgiveness is all about love. Where love abounds, there forgiveness will not tarry\n\n- Bangambiki Habyarimana, Pearls Of Eternity\n|\nUnderstanding is a three edged sword: your side, their side, and the truth.\n\n- J.\n|\nFor all those landscapes, those flowers and those plowed fields, the oldest of lands, show you every spring that there are things you cannot choke in blood.\n\n- Albert Camus, Resistance, Rebellion and Death: Essays\n|\nThough mountains melt and oceans burn,The gifts of love shall still return.\n\n- Rosamund Hodge, Cruel Beauty\n|\nThe dogs brought it all back to, you know, to the human side.\n\n- Luis Carlos Montalván, Until Tuesday: A Wounded Warrior and the Golden Retriever Who Saved Him\n|\nIn order to be successful you must decide to be intentional about what you do, how you live, and who you are becoming.\n\n- Mensah Oteh, Unlocking Life's Treasure Chest: Wisdom keys to keep you inspired, encouraged, motivated and focused\n|\nThis is our life; dreams come true, and dreams stumble, while others dreams remain postponed perpetuity.\n\n- Eyden\n|\nTry not to trip,' she added. 'We don't have time for a concussion today.'I groaned. That would be just like me - ruin everything, destroy the world, in a moment of klutziness.\n\n- Stephenie Meyer, New Moon\n|\nListen to the sunset...see its pretty hue... When you see it, think of me...and I'll think of you...\n\n- Oksana\n|\nRe-programming your mind, body & spirit is like planting a garden, if the soil isn't right nothing will grow.\n\n- Nikki\n|\nAh, yes, choice. I chose to let my ghosts stay in past. Past is history you know. Living is now. I sat. I breathed. I let past go. I let future go. I am. That is all.\n\n- Natalie Wright, Emily's 