o.\n\n- Sue\n|\nPeople just weren't interesting. Maybe they weren't supposed to be. But animals, birds, even insects were. I couldn't understand it.\n\n- Charles Bukowski, Hollywood\n|\nKeep in mind my friend, if an answer is not rational, then it is not an answer, but a delusion.\n\n- Abhijit Naskar, Human Making is Our Mission: A Treatise on Parenting\n|\nHmm…now that I think about it, housecats are often coddled and petted. You don’t pet me nearly enough. You must be a lax owner. How selfish of you to deprive your cat of attention.\n\n- Colleen\n|\nMaybe if we focused on being light & less on the dark, we might actually see things change.\n\n- Michael\n|\nLet a smile be your umbrella, and you'll end up with a face full of rain.\n\n- George\n|\nThe future is unlimited for you right now, no one can knows what you capable of. Do not surrender! Only you are capable to change the world.\n\n- Kamal\n|\nChase your stars fool, life is short.\n\n- Atticus Poetry, Love Her Wild: Poems\n|\nSilence is so steadfast, you know. It is so ample, after all.\n\n- Alice Fulton, The Nightingales of Troy: Stories of One Family's Century\n|\nWatching you has taught me that a man need not be weak to have a faith, but is made strong by it.\n\n- Roseanna M. White, A Stray Drop of Blood\n|\nI am here, I will always be here. Watching you, loving you.\n\n- Jayson\n|\nPerfection of character is this: to live each day as if it were your last, without frenzy, without apathy, without pretence.\n\n- Marcus Aurelius, Meditations\n|\nCount your blessings take care of the people you love.'Happy father's day to all the greatest POP,DAD,KIN in the world.\n\n- Napz\n|\nYou don’t get rich writing science fiction. If you want to get rich, you start a religion.\n\n- L.\n|\nIf you push me far enough, all I really know is that he was a fine fisherman.''You know more than that,' my father said. 'He was beautiful.\n\n- Norman Maclean, A River Runs Through It and Other Stories\n|\nWe'd stared into the face of 